        <sect1>
            <title>Skills</title>
            
            <para>
                Your skills are measured on a scale of one upwards. Generally, a score of four
                is considered to be a professional level, and eight is considered to be at a
                master level. Skills at higher scores are possible, with the best masters in the
                world having scores in the range of 10 to 15.
            </para>
            
            <para>
                You begin play with a number of skills according to the templates that you chose
                for your <e>Race</e>, <e>Background</e> and <e>Career</e>. You may have some
                extra points to put on skills after that as well, to allow you to perform some
                final customisations.
            </para>
            
            <para>
                Skills can be raised with <e>Experience</e>, which is gained during play. The
                amount of <e>Experience</e> needed to raise a skill to the next level is equal
                to the next level. So to raise a skill from four to five, will cost five
                experience.
            </para>
            
